    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-07-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-07-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="887"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d887">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.51 Public Works Debt/318</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Messersmith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 508</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-02">July 2,
                            1940</date>.<lb/>[Received July 3.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With further reference to the plan to settle the
                    remainder of the public works debt, I have the honor to report that, according
                    to today’s press, the House of Representatives met yesterday and adjourned until
                    July 18. It is obvious, therefore, that the House of Representatives, at least,
                    will give no further consideration to either of the bills to settle the public
                    works debt until after that date.</p>
                <p>The Senate, of course, has not met since it received its powers to legislate from
                    the Constituent Assembly, and there is no reason to believe that it intends to
                    meet until sometime after presidential elections on July 14.</p>
                <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">George S. Messersmith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
